cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with deep neural networks for scanpath prediction on 360-degree images, which is a task related to computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel representation of saliency information and uses back-propagation and binary cross-entropy loss, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the advantages of using saliency volumes and how they can be used for related tasks, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper deals with 360-degree images, which are a type of multimedia content, suggesting cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible sub-category.
